<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bahrain's Government Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain's government resigned Sunday
as a prelude to a proposed cabinet reshuffle next week, diplomatic
sources in Manama, capital of Bahrain, told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Bahraini Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Isa al-Khalifa accepted the
resignation tendered by Prime Minister Sheikh Khalifa Bin Sulman
al-Khalifa, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A new government is expected to be announced by Monday.
However, no major changes will be introduced to the new
cabinet with a view to maintaining stability in the tiny island
nation.
</P>
<P>
It is the second cabinet reshuffle in the country since 1995.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet reshuffle is a constitutional procedure that is
expected to take place after the demise of Bahraini Emir Sheikh
Isa Bin Salman al-Khalifa due to a sudden heart attack on March 6,
said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The mourning period in the Arab Gulf country will come to an
end in one week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
