<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Ministers To Meet On Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the 15-nation
European Union (EU) are to meet here in Brussels on Monday to
discuss Balkan issue during their monthly General Affairs Council.
</P>
<P>
The 15 ministers will debate the measures in regard to a
Stabilization and Association process for the countries of
south-eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, EU's executive body, had proposed a
series of bilateral Stabilization and Association Agreements
between the EU and the countries most affected by the crisis in
Kosovo as its contribution to a Stability Pact for the Balkan.
</P>
<P>
"The idea is the brainchild of the current German Presidency of
the European Union, and it was discussed at a meeting of the
countries concerned on May 27 in Bonn," the EU executive said.
</P>
<P>
European Commissioner Hans van den Broek said that this type of
agreement would give Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia, the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
and Albania a "political signal with regard to the possibility of
one day being integrated into the structures of the European Union
as part of a long-term effort". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
