<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-30 17:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saddam Meets With Indian Oil Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein on
Sunday met with visiting Indian Minister of Petroleum
K. Ramamurthy, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The Indian minister conveyed a letter from Indian caretaker
Prime Minister Bihari Vajpayee to Saddam, which deals with means
of enhancing the relations between the two countries, especially
in the oil, health and agricultural fields.
</P>
<P>
Ramamurthy who arrived here on Friday evening, thanked the
Iraqi government for its clear position toward the situation in
the South Asian subcontinent.
</P>
<P>
Saddam said that both India and Iraq are Asian countries, and
the evils in the world have vital interests in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Colonial countries do not believe in dialog and negotiation
to arrive at balanced relations," said Saddam, adding that "we
know these evil octopuses" will confront Iraq because Iraq and
India have common features.
</P>
<P>
On the Indian-Pakistani relations, Saddam said the U.S. wants
to push the two countries to military conflicts in order to tell
other countries that it is their nuclear potentialities that
have brought them the calamities.
</P>
<P>
The Indian minister said that India is fully aware that
military escalation with Pakistan will lead to the
U.S. intervention and deterioration of the situation in this
region.
</P>
<P>
Disputes between India and Pakistan over Kashmir have
escalated into military conflicts since Wednesday as Indian
warplanes began bombing targets in the Indian-controlled part of
Kashmir on account of Pakistan's infiltration attempts.
</P>
<P>
On the U.S.-led NATO aggression on Yugoslavia, the Iraqi
president said the U.S. covers the aggression on Yugoslavia with
a vain pretext that they are defending Muslims in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Observers here say that during the Indian oil minister's
visit, Iraq and India will sign an agreement on oil
cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
