<HEADLINE> Newly-Born Babies Die in Zambia Due to Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 30 (Xinhua) -- An undisclosed number of newly-born
babies have died in Zambia's biggest University Teaching Hospital,
because of the five- day-old strike, the television of the Zambia
National Broadcasting Corporation reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The babies died because no hospital worker attended to them and
in- patients said they have not been served with food since the
strike started on May 26.
</P>
<P>
Pregnant women also complained that labor wards are closed at
night and there are nobody attending to them.
</P>
<P>
Some other women who came to the hospital for antenatal care
have been turned away.
</P>
<P>
The striking workers said they will not resume their work until
their demand for a 30-percent-salary-increase backdated to this
January is met and the arrears are paid. 
</P>
