<HEADLINE> EDS-With Details Chinese, Malaysian Foreign Ministers Hold Talks (Details Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan and visiting Malaysian Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar
held fruitful talks on bilateral ties and other international and
regional issues of common interest here today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides believed that enhancing comprehensive cooperation
will not only serve the interests of both sides, but also be
conducive to peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
They said the joint statement on future bilateral cooperation
signed minutes before has drawn up a blueprint for bilateral
friendly and mutually beneficial cooperation and can direct the
long-term, stable and healthy development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
They stressed that existing disputes should be solved through
friendly consultations instead of carrying out too drastic actions.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that disputes between nations in the region should
be solved through channels of bilateral peaceful negotiations, and
that there should be no external interference in those disputes,
not to mention the internationalizing of them.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also exchanged views on the Kosovo issue,
agreeing that political negotiation is the only correct way to
solve the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian side hoped China will continue to play an
important role in the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
