<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
today's diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
Sino-Malaysian Cooperation
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and visiting Malaysian
Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar held talks and signed a joint
statement on framework for future bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The statement highlighted in enhancing bilateral cooperation in
politics, economy, culture, education and defense.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that their existing disputes should be
solved through discussion instead of carrying drastic actions, and
external interference should not be allowed, neither should those
conflicts be internationalized.
</P>
<P>
Meets Between Chinese, Russian Military Leaders
</P>
<P>
China and Russia bear historic responsibilities for upholding
justice and maintaining peace, Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission, said when meeting with visiting
Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Russian Armed Forces
Valiedin Korapierinykof.
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou, the chief of General Staff of China's People's
Liberation Army, also met with Korapierinykof, and criticized the
U.S. for attempting to establish a single-pole world that it
dominates, saying that it will surely result in strong objections
from all peace-loving people in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Russian visitor said that Russia will enhance coordination
and cooperation with China in order to promote friendly and
cooperative military relations within the framework of the
cooperative Russia-China strategic partnership and contribute to
maintaining peace in the region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Meets Argentine Official
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people cannot be bullied and any attempt to
threaten or blackmail the nation is doomed to failure, Chinese
Defense Minister Chi Haotian said during a meeting with Carlos
Maria Zabala, Joint Chief of Staff of Argentina's Armed Forces and
Chief of Staff of the Navy of Argentina.  
</P>
