<HEADLINE> Chinese Middle School Students Asked to Avoid Cigarettes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, may 31 (Xinhua) -- Several thousand primary and middle
school students in Xining, capital of northwestern China's Qinghai
Province, put their names on a letter today that asks their fellow
students elsewhere in the province to avoid the smoking habit.
</P>
<P>
The letter was one of the activities for World No-Tobacco Day.
Its headline was "Health, Not Smoking" and its purpose was to
support the no smoking activities at schools across the province,
where the smoking rate among middle and primary school students is
already 4.31 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province's patriotic health campaign committee and
education departments in Xining also began a large-scale education
program to help students avoid or give up smoking.  
</P>
