<HEADLINE> OAU Team to Observe South African Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) announced Monday that it has dispatched a 65-member
observer team to observe the June 2, 1999 national and provincial
elections in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here by the OAU Information Division
said the observer mission which is composed of government and
electoral officials from various OAU member states and staff
members of the OAU is led by professor Nicephore Soglo, former
President of the Republic of Benin who is already in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The OAU mission, has been deployed in all the nine provinces of
 South Africa as from May 30, 1999 and will remain in the country
until June 5, 1999, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The coming June 2 elections in South Africa is the second
all-race national elections since the establishment of New South
Africa in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
