<HEADLINE> Posters to Mark Macao's Return Chosen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese State Council's
Information Office and the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office have
approved five posters that will be put up for the return of Macao
to the motherland in December this year.
</P>
<P>
Some organizations have already begun printing copies of the
posters and will send them to major Chinese cities and Chinese
embassies and consulates abroad, an Information Office official
said here today.
</P>
