<HEADLINE> UAE Calls for Restraint Between India, Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
Monday called on India and Pakistan to exercise restraint and
make efforts to resolve the differences between them over the
Kashmir issue.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after its weekly session, the UAE
Cabinet urged the two countries to intensify direct talks and
respond to the diplomatic initiatives undertaken by U.N. Secretary
General Kofi Annan to defuse the crisis, the official WAM news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed the importance of stability in the
region for the benefit of the peoples in the two countries, WAM
said.
</P>
<P>
Indian warplanes last week began air strikes on the disputed
Kashmir area to flush out "infiltrators" India said backed by
Pakistan's armed forces, sharply raising tensions on the
nuclear-armed subcontinent.
</P>
<P>
Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee has turned down the
proposal by Annan to send an envoy to the region. 
</P>
