<HEADLINE> More Girls Attending School in Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- More girls are attending
school in the northern Chinese province of Hebei thanks to two
assistance projects.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show 99.8 percent of school age girls in the
province attending school, a figure that has caught up with male
children.
</P>
<P>
"Project Hope" and the "Chunlei Program" are the two projects
that have helped make this possible, a provincial official said
today.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 300 Hope schools have been built in the province
with money from the projects and 100,000 children have been able
to return to school as a result.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, about 99.1 percent of school age girls in the province
went to school, or 0.3 percentage points fewer than boys, and
figure became 99.8 percent by the end of last year, when girls
accounted for 48.9 percent of all students in the province.
</P>
</TEXT>
