<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Structure Reform Committee Meeting Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Coordinating Committee on
Market Structure Reform had a fruitful and constructive discussion
on issues related to the proposed demutualization and merger of
the Exchanges and Clearing Houses during its second meeting here
today.
</P>
<P>
After two hours of discussion, members of the committee reached
a consensus on the broad direction in the further structuring of
various aspects of NewCo, the new share holding company to be set
up as the result of the demutualization and merger.
</P>
<P>
Convened by Rafael Hui, secretary for Financial Services, the
meeting also discussed issues on the corporate governance of NewCo,
the trading rights of current members of the exchanges and access
to the market under NewCo, matters relating to the clearing houses,
and the future regulatory framework.
</P>
<P>
Members also discussed the optimal regulatory role of NewCo.
</P>
<P>
The meeting agreed that while NewCo must perform certain
aspects of front-line regulatory work in order to achieve quality
assurance which was essential to attract business, regulatory
overlaps should be avoided as far as possible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
