<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese City Begins Minimum Wage Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Labor Administration of
Shenzhen, China's most famous special economic zone (SEZ), has
announced that it will implement a minimum monthly wage this year
of 430 yuan (about 50 U.S. dollars) within urban areas affected by
state SEZ policies.
</P>
