<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Head Meets Senior Russian Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, the chief of General
Staff of China's People's Liberation Army, in a meeting here today
with Deputy Chief of General Staff of the Russian Armed Forces
Valiedin Korapierinykof, said that ties between the Chinese and
Russian armed forces have gone smoothly along with the Sino-
Russian strategic cooperative partnership.
</P>
<P>
Hegemony and power politics have made new developments in spite
of the fact that the global situation is changing toward
relaxation, Fu said, adding that the NATO bombing of Yugoslavia,
which has gone on for more than 60 days, has put into practice the
strategic new concept put forward by NATO during its 50th
anniversary conference.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. attempt to establish a single-pole world that it
dominates will surely result in strong objections from all peace-
loving people in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Korapierinykof said that the strategic cooperative partnership
mapped out by top Chinese and Russian leaders has laid a solid
foundation for the development of friendship and cooperation
between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. tries every way to obstruct the multi-polarization
process because it sets the U.S. ambition to dominate the world
back, he said, but Russia will work with China in contributing to
bilateral ties and to safeguarding world peace and stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
