<HEADLINE> Beijing Tearing Down Buildings Without Permits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- For the 50th anniversary of the
People's Republic and to give it a more beautiful look,
authorities in the Chinese capital have demolished more than 3
million square meters of buildings that do not have proper
authorization.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Dongming, the director of the Municipal Comprehensive
Environment Management Office, said today that 2.85 million sq.m.
of these buildings are in the city proper and that they are a
major source of disorder and seriously harm the city's appearance
and image.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, Beijing had 7.3 million sq.m. of such
buildings, he said, and the demolition work will continue. A third
of the land that is left when they are torn down will be planted
with grass and flowers and the rest will be paved with colorful
bricks. 
</P>
