<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province Gives Tractors To Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of Xingtai,
a city in north China's Hebei Province shipped 60 tractors today
to Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, as a gift for
the Tibetan people.
</P>
<P>
Xingtai was badly damaged by an earthquake 33 years ago that
killed more than 8,000 people and destroyed 1.2 million houses,
and Tibet, even though it was poor at the time, donated 240 horses
to Xingtai to help the disaster victims rebuild their lives.
</P>
<P>
"We were very much moved when a group of Tibetans took the
horses themselves to Xingtai in spite of the great distance and
difficulties 33 years ago," said Wang Santang, a deputy Party
chief of Xingtai, who was in charge of the tractor shipping.
</P>
<P>
The gift was presented to mark the 40th anniversary of the
democratic reform of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the tractors represent the friendship and unity
between the Tibetan and Han people and will contribute to Tibet's
economy," he concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
