</P>
<P>
ACDP: African Christian Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
In the 1994 elections, the ANC won seven of the nine provinces
in the country while the NP and the IFP won Western Cape and
KwaZulu-Natal respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to recent opinion polls, however, the IFP will lose
its major support base in the new election, and the ANC and the NP
are expected to have a neck-to-neck race in the Western Cape. The
ANC will win the other seven provinces. 
</P>
