<HEADLINE> Central China's Free Consultation on How to Quit Smoking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A special telephone line was
opened today in Hunan Province, central China, for free smoking
consultation service, the first of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey by the Hunan Provincial Institute of Health
Education showed that the province has more than 20 million
smokers, or nearly 30 percent of its population.
</P>
<P>
Although some 80 percent of the smokers say they'd like to quit
smoking, but fewer than three percent are able to succeed, so the
consultation line was set up to give scientific advice to those
who want to give up smoking.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
