<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs Has New Way to Promote Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Customs office
explained 10 new measures today which it hopes will help increase
exports in the region.
</P>
<P>
These include using a universal customs declaration this year
and keeping a record of enterprises' histories so that the more
law-abiding ones will have their papers processed faster.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials say the move will make things more convenient
for export-oriented enterprises and improve the management of
customs.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of this year, Shanghai's exports were
worth 5 billion U.S. dollars, up 17.4 percent from the same period
of last year.  
