absolutely a bad habit," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He called upon all concerned including mass media, opinion
leaders and cinema artists to come forward with anti-smoking
campaigns to reduce the number of smokers.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 80,000 people die of tobacco-related diseases every year
in Bangladesh, and at the present, there are about 18 million
smokers in Bangladesh spending 10 million taka (about 206,00 U.S.
dollars) a day buying cigarettes, estimated ADHUNIK, a national
anti-tobacco organization of Bangladesh. 
