<HEADLINE> Russian President Makes More Government Appointments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
named Viktor Khristenko as first deputy prime minister on Monday
in the final touches to the formation of the government of Sergei
Stepashin.
</P>
<P>
Khristenko, once a deputy prime minister in the Sergei
Kiriyenko cabinet, replaces Mikhail Zadornov, who resigned last
week after his request to remain as finance minister was rejected
by Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Zadornov was named special negotiator with international
financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The other appointments made on Monday included Ilya Glbebanov
as deputy prime minister, Andrei Shapovalyants as economics
minister, Ilya Yuzhanov as minister for anti-trust policy and
Vladimir Vasilyev as deputy secretary of the security council.
</P>
