<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Flat on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed flat on
Singapore Stock Market Monday as later losses offset earlier gains
in the absence of institutional activities.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index inched up 0.18 points to end
at 1,903.86, managing to maintain its grip on the key 1,900-point
level.
</P>
<P>
In total, some 1,330.8 million units worth some 1,020.63
million Singapore dollars (about 591.50 million U.S. dollars)
changed hands as gainers led losers by 273 to 81 while another 90
counters closed unchanged.
</P>
<P>
IPC hogged the volume list with 69.08 million shares traded. It
was followed by Hotung that had 44.35 million units done. Li Xin
was the next with 41.04 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH topped the actives list of the day as it ran up 70 cents to
close at 24.30 Singapore dollars, rebounding from a week of
continued sliding. F &AMP; N climbed up by 65 cents to finish at 7.45
Singapore dollars. Serial Sys picked up 42.5 cents to end at 1.05
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture led the descent of the day giving up
60 cents to close at 10.30 Singapore dollars. SIA F and Seaview
lost 40 cents each and finished at 15.00 and 10.00 Singapore
dollars respectively. CityDev shed 30 cents to end at 10.00
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said Friday's rise on Wall Street and the increase in
April's manufacturing output released on the same day refrained
from giving a spur to the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
They said today's market sentiment was mixed with second liners
dominating overall activities while foreign investor activity
slowed ahead of holidays in the U.S. and the U.K.
</P>
<P>
They also noted inexpensive electronic stocks enjoyed attention
from investors with serial System recording a 61.5-percent surge.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
