<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Emblem of 2002 FIFA World Cup Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A launching ceremony for the emblem
of the 2002 FIFA World Cup Korea/Japan was held here Monday
afternoon with participation of more than 300 delegates.
</P>
<P>
The official emblem of the 2002 FIFA World Cup consists of two
key elements: the symbol and the logotype.
</P>
<P>
The symbol is the most important visual element, whereas the
logotype is the lettering used to convey the image of the World
Cup in a consistent manner.
</P>
<P>
Following is an introduction of the emblem.
</P>
<P>
In the middle of the emblem, there is a stylized representation
of the FIFA World Cup Trophy which symbolizes the unique image of
the FIFA World Cup as the element of the emblem. The trophy is one
of the two distinguishing figures supporting the globe.
</P>
<P>
The overall appearance of the emblem is one of a circle. It was
chosen for its highly symbolic nature: the circle has been part of
the Asian cultures for many centuries and also stands for the
universe, the sun, the world and even life. Thus the theme of a
circle and a sphere is used to consitute both the outer shape and
the World Cup Trophy at the center.
</P>
<P>
The symbol is brightly coloured to embody the vibrant colours
of the many different countries participating in the tournament.
Moreover, the yellow colour in the middle of emblem symblizes "
center" in Aisa and the white colour surrounding the trophy
symbolizes "purity".
</P>
<P>
The circle is left open at the left top of the emblem to
indicate openness of the World Cup Trophy to anyone in the world.
In other words, each and every participant has a chance of winning
the trophy.
</P>
<P>
The logotype consists of three parts: the year 2002, the FIFA
World Cup logo and the names of the host nations Korea and Japan.
Each has been designed to reflect the characteristics of the World
Cup from various perspectives.
</P>
<P>
The two zeros of the year 2002 are represented by a horizontal
"S", symbolizing "infinity" and embodying the spirit of eternal
unity and the harmonious link between Korea and Japan as well as
among the World Cup participants.
</P>
<P>
The FIFA WORLD CUP lettering is reserved for FIFA to use in
every tournament. And the 2002 FIFA WORLD CUP appears in golden
colour to represent dignity.
</P>
<P>
The lettering of the co-hosts' names combines a traditional
Asian style with a touch of modern sense. The names are in the
colour of their national flags. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Children Exhibit Greater Willingness to Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey revealed that
contemporary Chinese children are exhibiting less selfishness and
instead are displaying a greater willingness to share.
</P>
<P>
The obvious trend was revealed during a recent survey of
conducted in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, and Chongqing. The
survey covered 5,000 children between the ages of three and seven.
</P>
<P>
Most children born after the 1980s belong to one-child families
and have received kindergarten education enhancing their awareness
of the need to share.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed more than 55 percent of respondents voiced a
willingness to share, or loan toys and books to other children.
Only 3.1 percent of the respondents voiced dissatisfaction with
sharing joy and resisted sharing as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The tendency to share was even greater with older children.
Some 70 percent of respondents above the age of six years voiced
their willingness to share.
</P>
<P>
Education provided by society and families is extremely
important for guiding the behavior of children, a conclusion
clearly indicated by the fact that 26.5 percent of the respondents
noted their willingness to share or loan personal items.
</P>
<P>
The survey also showed that the Chinese children are basically
unable to take proper care of themselves. This in turn results in
weak character, heavy dependence and lack of awareness of the need
for personal improvement.
</P>
<P>
Some 35-40 percent of respondents lacked the desire to dress
themselves, with more than 90 percent noting they would seek help
when facing difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises Index
rose 12.11 points to close at 418.99 today.
</P>
<P>
The index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of 40 China's state-owned enterprises listed on the
Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
New Hang Seng MidCap50 Index dropped 0.42 points from the
previous session to close at 833.91.
</P>
<P>
New Hang Seng MidCap50 Index comprises 50 stocks ranked from
101 to 150 on the Hong Kong bourse in terms of market
capitalization and turnover.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index gained 9.34
points to close at 933.16.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index tracks the
performance of 48 locally-listed companies with a significant
equity interest held by entities in China.
</P>
<P>
The three segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank.  
</P>
