<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 87.87
points, or 0.73 percent, to close at 12,147.12 today.
</P>
<P>
Stocks for Finance, Utilities and Properties respectively rose
by 1.02 percent, 0.82 percent and 1.88 percent while the Commerce
and Industry share suffered a loss of 0.94 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went up 2.98 percent and
the Hang Seng China-affiliated Corporations Index up 1.01 percent.
</P>
<P>
Today's market turnover was 4.022 billion HK dollars (516
million U.S. dollars), 1.551 billion HK dollars (199 million U.S.
dollars) less than that of Friday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index edged up 29.54 points, or 0.24 percent,
to open at 12,088.79 today.
</P>
<P>
The HSI lost 10.69 points, or 0.09 percent, to finish the
morning session at 12,048.56.  
