<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Registers Some 1.5b U.S. Dollar Deficit in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region government reported today a deficit of 11,
417.4 million HK dollars (1,463.8 million U.S. dollars) for April
1999.
</P>
<P>
Announcing its financial results for the month that ended on
April 30, 1999, the government said that expenditure for the first
month of the current financial year amounted to 24,725.3 million
HK dollars (3,169.9 million U.S. dollars) and revenue to 13,307.9
million HK dollars (1,706.1 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
During the month, the government injected 8,500 million HK
dollars (1,089.7 million U.S. dollars) of capital into the Kowloon-
Canton Railway Corporation for the West Rail Project.
</P>
<P>
The fiscal reserves stood at 422,885 million HK dollars (54,216
million U.S. dollars) as of April 30, 1999, a decrease of 11,417.4
million HK dollars (1,462.5 million U.S. dollars) compared with
the balance of 434,302.4 million HK dollars (55,679.8 million U.S.
dollars) as of March 31, 1999, the end of the previous financial
year.
</P>
<P>
The aforesaid balance as of March 31, 1999 is slightly higher
than the provisional figure of 434,269.7 million HK dollars (55,
675.6 million U.S. dollars) announced on April 30, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
