<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 09:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in recent operations staged by
the Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, an official
statement said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said the security forces had wiped out two PKK militants at
Buyukciftlik village, four at Duztepe area in Yuksekova town and
one in Semdinli town of Hakkari province and three in Cudi
Mountain region of Sirnak province.
</P>
<P>
One soldier of the security forces was also killed in the
armed clashes with the PKK in the southeast, added the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added that the security forces had captured one PKK
militant in the Dargecit town of Mardin province.
</P>
<P>
Conflicts between the Turkish government and the PKK have
claimed over 37,000 lives since the PKK started fighting for
an independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Turkish government has beefed up security
measures on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near Turkey's western
province of Bursa where the trial is expected to open on Monday
for PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan on charges of treason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
