Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- NATO killed at least 11 civilians last weekend when it
bombed a bridge with missiles in Varvarin, 160 kilometers south of
Belgrade. Meanwhile, the Western military alliance said it was
waiting for ``concrete'' action by Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic who, while accepting the principles of the Group of
Eight on ending the Kosovo conflict, seems to exclude NATO from a
future security force.
</P>
<P>
