<HEADLINE> CCB to Expand Support for Telecommunications Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB)
announced today that it will provide 3.6 billion yuan in this
year's first round of buyer's credits to support the
telecommunications industry.
</P>
<P>
A CCB spokesman said that buyer's credits for purchasing
telecommunications equipment have been listed as the key for the
bank's credit business during the year.
</P>
<P>
He said the CCB will not only continue to support domestic
telecommunications equipment manufacturers, but will also expand
its buyer's credit service to cover some sino-overseas joint
ventures, including Shanghai Bell Alcatel, Beijing Nokia and
Suzhou Nokia.
</P>
<P>
Buyer's credits will enable telecommunications service
providers to purchase domestically manufactured telecommunications
equipment. The CCB initiated the business service in May 1998 and
granted buyer's credits totaling 4.8 billion yuan by the end of
that same year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the CCB has recently adopted buyer's credit
operating procedures to further standardize the service and ensure
the quality of related loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
