<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Accelerates Connection of Major Power Grids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The linking of China's major power
grids by 2020 will make it possible to achieve nationwide power
exchanges, according to the China State Power Corporation (CSPC).
</P>
<P>
The nation's rapid economic development has sparked a new stage
in power development characterized by expanded capacity and large
grids, according to a CSPC official.
</P>
<P>
China has developed six large power grids and a group of
provincial grids with transmission lines stretching 567,000
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Power Station will link power grids nationwide,
said the official, adding that the station will provide power for
areas in central and north China, as well as Sichuan grids. The
stations will not only help form the Great Central China Power
Grid spanning a distance of 2,000 km from east to west, but will
also serve as a link to grids in north, northwest and south China.
</P>
<P>
Thermal power production bases in Shanxi, Shaanxi and Jiangxi
provinces will ensure large power supplies for Beijing, Tianjin,
Tangshan, Baoding and other cities in northeast China, according
to the official.
</P>
<P>
He added that all of the country's major power grids will be
linked between 2010-2020. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
