<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Growth of Telecommunications Industry Slowing Down in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China's fast-growing
telecommunications industry has slowed down its pace in the first
quarter this year, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Production of optical communication equipment increased by 9.3
percent on an annual basis to 3,780 units, and that of carrier
communication equipment went down 11.5 percent to 1,442 units, the
bureau said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the output of program-controlled switchboards
soared 50.8 percent year on year to 7.85 million lines.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 4.97 million sets of mobile communication
equipment between January and March, 41 percent more than the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Production of computers during the time enjoyed a 113 percent
increase to a total of 398 units while that of micro-computers
surged 46 percent to 707,600.
</P>
<P>
Computer manufacturers in China have enjoyed a rapid growth
these years, and recent surveys show that more and more Chinese
are planning to buy their own personal computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
