<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Industrial Output Value Leading in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, the south China
economic powerhouse, topped other provinces of the country in
terms of industrial output value in the first quarter this year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that Guangdong's
industrial output value in the January-March period stood at 207
billion yuan (25 billion U.S. dollars), surging 13.6 percent on an
annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Following Guangdong are Jiangsu Province, with an industrial
output value of 178 billion yuan, and Shanghai Municipality with
122 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A close neighbor of Hong Kong, Guangdong is the first province
in the country that opens to the outside world. The province has
developed a high level of processing industry and a large
proportion of its enterprises are export-oriented.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
