<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Total Investment Up in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Total investment in China in the
first quarter this year hit 202 billion yuan (24.4 billion U.S.
dollars), surging 22.7 percent year on year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 118 billion yuan (14 billion dollars) went to
capital construction, soaring 28.1 percent, and 33 billion yuan (4
billion dollars) was made for technical upgrading and
transformation, up 13.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate investment in scientific research and poly-
technical services from January to March reached 622 million yuan
(75 million dollars), an increase of 19.4 percent on an annual
basis.
</P>
<P>
Investment in education, culture, health care, broadcasting and
social welfare amounted to 7.5 billion yuan (906 million dollars),
soaring 35.4 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has put the development of science and
education high on the agenda, with a view to pacing up the
country's modernization process.
</P>
<P>
In terms of regions, Guangdong Province, the economic
powerhouse in south China, had the largest amount of investment of
33 billion yuan (4 billion dollars). Shaanxi enjoyed the fastest
increase among all provinces and autonomous regions, with its
investment skyrocketing 83.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
