<HEADLINE> Citizens in Shenzhen Earn More in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The people in the south China city
of Shenzhen continued to enjoy the highest income among the 35
major Chinese cities, according to the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Statistics offered by the bureau show that the per capita
monthly income in China's southern boomtown Shenzhen hit 3,023
yuan in February, and the per capita disposable income reached 3,
001 yuan while the city's per capita living expenditure stood high
at 1,676 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city was followed by Guangzhou and Hangzhou in per capita
annual income and disposable income. The per capita monthly income
in Guangzhou was 1,541 yuan and that of Hangzhou stood at 1,320
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The average per capita monthly income of 35 major Chinese
cities stood at 888 yuan, with the per capita monthly disposable
income at 885 yuan and per capita living expenditure at 638 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, neighboring Hong Kong, is China's first special
economic zone. 
</P>
