<HEADLINE> EDS-CMC-Russian CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Russian Senior Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission (CMC), said here today that China and
Russia, permanent members of the UN Security Council and
influential countries, bear historic responsibilities for
upholding justice and maintaining peace.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the Chinese government hopes to further
enhance consultations with Russia in a joint effort to promote the
development of worldwide multi-polarization and establish a new
international political and economic order.
</P>
