<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Offers $75 mln Aid for Mozambique's Rural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has decided
to offer Mozambique 75 million U.S. dollars to help repair the
roads and develop in central and northern parts of the country, an
EU official said.
</P>
<P>
Jaxier Puyol, EU representative to Mozambique, said Saturdays
during his tour to Zambezia, a province in central Mozambique,
about 30 million dollars of the aid will be used for rural
development programs in Zambezia, Cabo Delgado and Inhambane
provinces, the Noticias daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The aims of the rural programs, Puyol said, is to improve the
infrastructure facilities and the social conditions, especially in
sectors like education, health, water supply and roads.
</P>
<P>
The EU official said that the other 45 million dollars will be
used to project of Zambezia-Nampula road repair, which is expected
to start next year.
</P>
<P>
Zambezia is the focus of EU's aid, for which EU has channeled
30 percent of its annual aid, about 100 million dollars, to
Mozambique, Puyol said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
