<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sees Expanding Industrial Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial sector continued
to grow in the first quarter this year, according to figures
released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The added value of industry from January to March increased by
10.1 percent on an annual basis to 447 billion yuan (54 billion U.
S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
The added value of light industry during the period stood at
187.5 billion yuan and that of heavy industry 259.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed an added value of 257.5 billion yuan from the
state owned and state holding enterprises, which accounted for
more than half of the gross industrial output in the three months.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, collectively-owned enterprises, a component of
the public assets, reported an added value of 74.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The added value of enterprises with foreign investment and
investment from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan amounted to 88.3
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The statistics covered all enterprises in the state and non-
state sectors with the annual product sales revenue at and above
five million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
