<HEADLINE> UAE-France Trade Up in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between the
United Arab Emirates (UAE) and France grew by 18 percent in 1998
compared to the previous year, the Gulf News daily reported on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
French exports to the UAE in 1998 were valued at 1.2 billion
U.S. dollars, according to Jean-Francois Thibault, French
ambassador to the UAE.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said French imports, mainly oil-related, were
dependent on the policies of the UAE government.
</P>
<P>
French exports to the UAE in the first quarter of this year
jumped 30 percent over the same quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
"Economic relations between France and the UAE are getting
stronger and the UAE is close to becoming France's third largest
trading partner in the Middle East after Egypt and Saudi Arabia,"
the ambassador said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
