<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 27 Injured in Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 27 others
injured in a tube gas explosion late Sunday night in Istanbul, the
largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occured when four people were trying to control
the gas leak out of the tube at a coffee house in the Beyoglu
district of Istanbul, but the tube suddenly exploded, killing one
person and injuring 27 others including three children and three
women, the local Hurriyet (Freedom) daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to Taksim Hospital for treatment, said
the paper, adding three of them are in serious conditions. 
</P>
