<HEADLINE> Nepali Cabinet Takes Oath </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Krishna
Prasad Bhattarai and his 15 cabinet ministers took oath Monday
before King Birendra.
</P>
<P>
This is the first majority government in Nepal in the past four
and a half years.
</P>
<P>
Bhattarai was appointed prime minister last Thursday after his
Nepali Congress won a majority of 110 seats in the elections to
the 205-member House of Representatives held on May 3 and May 17.
</P>
<P>
He said that the cabinet will be expanded in three phases.
</P>
<P>
Under the kingdom's constitution, the new government has to
obtain a vote of confidence in the house within 30 days. 
</P>
