<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Notaries Public Granted Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Justice issued
certificates today to 38 Hong Kong notaries public who will
continue to serve as appointed attesting officers.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony held in Shenzhen, Vice-Minister of Justice Duan
Zhengkun said the system to appoint Hong Kong attesting officers "
settles the question of using legal documents in both inland areas
and Hong Kong which have different legal systems and thereby
safeguards the legitimate rights and interests of parties
concerned."
</P>
<P>
He urged the new attesting officers to be faithful to law and
responsibilities to society and clients when discharging their
duties in order to contribute more to exchanges and ensuring the
common prosperity of inland areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Attesting officers applying for new terms upon expiration of
their terms will be examined and assessed, with qualified
individuals appointed in succession.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Justice introduced the system to appoint
attesting officers in Hong Kong in 1981. Over 200 Hong Kong
lawyers appointed to positions as attesting officers have handled
some 500,000 inland legal cases involving Hong Kong residents,
according to the ministry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
