<HEADLINE> hke053116 - Indian Air Strikes Continue for Sixth Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Indian Air Force (IAF) continued
its air strikes in the Kargil sector of Kashmir for the sixth day
Monday, Defense Ministry sources said here.
</P>
<P>
The air strikes in fact continued overnight unstopped in the
area, while Indian army and Pakistan army regulars were also
having close combat at the same place.
</P>
<P>
The Indian side has claimed to have killed about 400 intruders
backed by Pakistan in the past few days. Indian casualties were
estimated at 33 killed, 130 wounded and 12 missing.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of four IAF personnel, who were killed last Friday
when their helicopter was downed by "infiltrators" in the Drass
sector of Kashmir, were flown to Sarsawa air base in Uttar Pradesh
Sunday night and would be cremated later Monday. 
</P>
