midnight Saturday to Sunday, NATO war planes bombed many targets
in the outskirts of Belgrade and the southern part of the Serb
Republic, in particular targets in Kosovo, killing one and
wounding six.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday morning, NATO planes bombed Belgrade with 15 missiles
and pounded civilian targets in the Serb Republic. NATO missiles
also hit a bridge in the Serbian town of Varvarin on Sunday,
killing at least 11 people, the station said. 
