<HEADLINE> Community Health Service Flourishing in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A community health service
management scheme which includes a series of training programs for
practitioners has been launched today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has asked governments at different
levels to develop urban public health service systems and
establish a community health service network.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, public health departments have largely gone
along with the proposal and increased community public health
input, and provided convenient and low-cost medical care for
residents.
</P>
<P>
A community health service network has been developed in a
number of large and medium sized cities in China. Tianjin has
already provided training for practitioners; Shanghai has combined
its community health service with other services and Harbin has
strengthened its network of medical centers. 
</P>
