<HEADLINE> China Moves to Tap Overseas Oil Markets (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China is actively exploring
international oil markets, alongside its consistent efforts to tap
huge oil and gas resources domestically by inviting foreign
partners.
</P>
<P>
In the coming years, China is expected to develop transitional
oil production focusing on the Middle East, Russia, and Central
Asia, according to Qin Anmin, president of the China Petroleum
Engineering Construction Enterprise Group (CPECEG).
</P>
<P>
Qin said that China plans to turn out 10 million tons of crude
oil through its overseas production by the turn of the century.
And by the year 2010, China will try to develop an annual overseas
oil production capacity of 50 million tons, in addition to an
annual gas supply of 50 billion cubic meters from abroad.
</P>
<P>
Presently, China is making headway in oil exploration and
development overseas. The China National Petroleum Corp. (CNPC)
and its subsidiary China Petroleum Engineering Construction
Enterprise Group (CPECEG) have successfully obtained the share-
holding, operational and leasing rights of oilfields in Peru,
Canada, Thailand, Kuwait and some other countries, and has turned
out a certain amount of crude oil.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China is enjoying great prospects in its oil and gas
production in Sudan and Russia. A cooperative gas project in
Central Asia area will hopefully provide China with 25 billion
cubic meters of gas a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990531.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Moves to Tap Overseas Oil Markets  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In line with a Sino-Russian cooperative gas project, China will
introduce 25 billion cu m of natural gas from eastern Siberia
yearly.
</P>
<P>
According to Qin, China has made marked progress in undertaking
oil projects overseas. The CPECEG has so far signed overseas oil
construction contracts totaling nearly 2 billion US dollars. It
has been listed among the world's top 225 contractors for five
consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that China is rich in oil resources,
producing over 150 million tons of crude oil annually and having
so far verified total oil deposits of 17 billion tons, ranking the
5th and 9th, respectively, in the world.
</P>
<P>
He explained that China's petroleum development strategy is to
rely mainly on domestic resources, speed up Sino-foreign
cooperation in exploring its offshore and western onshore oil and
gas resources, and step up efforts to tap international oil
markets. 
</P>
