<HEADLINE> China Conducts National Survey of Forest Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Satellite photographs are to be used
for first time in a national research of forest resources which
will begin shortly.
</P>
<P>
The photographs will support massive field investigations in a
bid to get a clearer picture of the extent of China's forests and
will then be used to evaluate and improve the government work on
forest protection, according to a national meeting on forest
protection held here.
</P>
<P>
The survey will cover all major protected forest and key
ecological areas. All research institutes under the State Forestry
Administration and all local forestry research institutes will
work together in the project.
</P>
<P>
The survey of forest areas is expected to be completed by
November while that into key ecological areas is expected to end
next February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
