<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Extend lead in Euro Qualifying Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Steffen Iversen's scored four
minutes into the game to give Norway a 1-0 victory over Georgia in
a European championship qualifier at Oslo on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory promoted Norway to 13 points from 6 games, five
more than second-placed Latvia who have a game in hand.
</P>
<P>
Iversen, a Tottenham Hotspur player, headed home a cross from
the left wing by Tore Andre Flo of Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
Georgia rarely posed threat on Norwegian goalkeeper Frode Olsen
in a game dominated by midfield duels. But Norway's forwards
squandered almost all their chances.
</P>
<P>
Georgian Temur Ketsbaya of Newcastle United almost equalised
early in the second half with a shot blasted from 20 meters that
was tipped over the bar by Olsen.
</P>
<P>
Norway were missing some key players in the match, including
Manchester United defender Ronny Johnson and striker Ole Gunnar
Solskjaer, who both have knee injuries. First choice goalkeeper
Thomas Myhre of Everton broke his ankle in training last week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
