<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Children's Picture Storybooks Popular Among Collectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Picture storybooks for children,
once indispensable for Chinese children, have become a popular
item for collectors.
</P>
<P>
Storybook collections are being exhibited in the city of
Tianjin, with more than 3,000 storybooks on display. The
exhibition was sponsored by the municipal history museum and a
collectors organization. It had exhibits from different periods
like the Republic of China (1912 -- 1949) and before and during
the so-called Cultural Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Also on show were picture storybooks on special topics, books
that have received awards, manuscripts, and research materials.
</P>
<P>
Picture storybooks became a collector's item only after the mid-
1980s, when many publishing houses stopped producing such books as
tastes changed among Chinese children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
