<HEADLINE> McCann Pulls out of Scot Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Rangers winger Neil McCann has
pulled out of Craig Brown's Scotland squad for the Euro 2000
qualifiers against the Faroe Islands and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
McCann limped out of Saturday's Cup final victory over Celtic
at Hampden Park with a recurrence of the knee injury which has
plagued his season.
</P>
<P>
And the SFA confirmed that the former Hearts man misses the
away qualifiers against the Faroes on Saturday and the Czech
Republic four days later -- a double header that will shape the
Scots' qualification dream.
</P>
<P>
Brown, who was already without Colin Hendry, has not yet called
up a replacement for McCann.
</P>
<P>
Hendry was ruled out with a groin problem that will require
surgery later this week.
</P>
<P>
The squad meets up on Monday morning and Brown may announce a
replacement for McCann then. 
